==English==
===Etymology===
Italian (''see Italian entry below'')

===Interjection===
'''bravo!'''

#Used to express appreciation, especially to a performer.

====Usage note====
Sometimes the Italian female form '''brava''' is used for a woman, and the Italian plural forms '''bravi''' and '''brave''' used to a group of men and a group containing at least one woman, respectively.

